# CampusHat Backend Audit Report

## Module 01: User Registration & Role Assignment
- **1.1 Default Role**: ✅ PASS. `User.role` has default `normal_user`. [UserRegistrationSerializer](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/serializers.py#22-83) does not hardcode it.
- **1.2 Email Verification**: ⚠️ WARN. [UserLoginSerializer](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/serializers.py#89-149) checks `is_email_verified=False`, but returns `400 BAD REQUEST` instead of `403 FORBIDDEN` as strictly expected by standard (though functionally correct).
- **1.3 Wallet Auto-Creation**: ✅ PASS. Auto-created via [signals.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/mall/signals.py) [create_user_wallet](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/signals.py#16-23).
- **1.4 Role Elevation**: ✅ PASS. [signals.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/mall/signals.py) correctly updates `user.role` to student/faculty upon verification approval.
- **1.5 Token Expiration**: ✅ PASS. [EmailVerificationToken](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/models.py#244-311) has `expires_at = timezone.now() + timedelta(hours=24)`.
- **1.6 Duplicate Email**: ✅ PASS. `User.email` is `unique=True` and `UserRegistrationSerializer.validate_email` raises 400.
- **1.7 Resend Verification**: ❌ FAIL. Cannot find endpoint for resending verification token (`resend-verification`).

## Module 02: JWT Authentication & Session Security
- **2.1 Access Token Expiry**: ✅ PASS. `ACCESS_TOKEN_LIFETIME` uses env `JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_LIFETIME_MINUTES` with default `15`.
- **2.2 Refresh Token Expiry**: ✅ PASS. `REFRESH_TOKEN_LIFETIME` uses env `JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN_LIFETIME_DAYS` with default `7`.
- **2.3 Refresh Token in HttpOnly Cookie**: ❌ FAIL. [UserLoginSerializer](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/serializers.py#89-149) returns tokens in the response body. [LoginView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/views.py#149-185) does not set HttpOnly cookies. XSS vulnerability is present.
- **2.4 Logout Blacklists Token**: ✅ PASS. [LogoutView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/views.py#206-250) calls `token.blacklist()` using `RefreshToken`.
- **2.5 Force Logout (Revoke All)**: ✅ PASS. The `DELETE /auth/sessions/revoke-all/` endpoint exists in [session_views.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/session_views.py).
- **2.6 Token from Revoked Session**: ❌ FAIL. Cannot find middleware validating `token_hash` against `user_sessions.revoked`.
- **2.7 Expired Sessions Cleanup**: ❌ FAIL. `cleanup_expired_sessions` Celery beat task is missing from [config/celery.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/config/celery.py).
- **2.8 Suspended User Auth**: ✅ PASS. `UserLoginSerializer.validate` checks `if not user.is_active` and SimpleJWT checks it implicitly during token validaton.

## Module 03: Role-Based Access Control
- **3A.1 GET /api/v1/mall/products/**: ✅ PASS. View uses `[AllowAny]`.
- **3A.2 GET /api/v1/mall/products/{slug}/**: ✅ PASS. View uses `[AllowAny]`. (N+1 query check for view count to be verified later).
- **3A.3 GET /api/v1/cart/**: ✅ PASS. View uses `[IsNormalUserOrAbove]`, correctly blocking guests.
- **3A.4 POST /api/v1/cart/add/**: ✅ PASS. View uses `[IsNormalUserOrAbove]`.
- **3A.5 POST /api/v1/orders/checkout/**: ✅ PASS. View uses `[IsNormalUserOrAbove]`.
- **3A.6 GET /api/v1/orders/**: ✅ PASS. Filter restricts to `Order.objects.filter(buyer=request.user)`.
- **3A.7 POST /api/v1/mall/products/**: ✅ PASS. Requires `[IsAuthenticated(), IsApprovedSeller()]`.
- **3A.8 PATCH /api/v1/mall/products/{slug}/**: ✅ PASS. Enforces owner check in view: `if product.store.seller.user != request.user: 403`.
- **3B.1 GET /api/v1/marketplace/listings/**: ✅ PASS. [MarketplaceProductListSerializer](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/marketplace/product_serializers.py#167-195) excludes contact fields completely.
- **3B.2 GET /api/v1/marketplace/listings/{id}/**: ✅ PASS. `MarketplaceProductDetailSerializer.get_user_info()` checks [IsVerifiedForMarketplace](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/core/permissions.py#131-155).
- **3B.3 POST /api/v1/marketplace/listings/**: ✅ PASS. Requires `[IsAuthenticated, IsVerifiedForMarketplace]`. (Seen in previous diffs)
- **3B.4 POST /api/v1/marketplace/chats/start/**: ✅ PASS. [StartChatView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/marketplace/chat_views.py#25-69) uses `[IsAuthenticated, IsVerifiedStudent]`. Actually, ⚠️ WARN. It requires [IsVerifiedStudent](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/core/permissions.py#11-32), which denies sellers/faculty who are [IsVerifiedForMarketplace](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/core/permissions.py#131-155). Fix needed.
- **3B.5 POST /api/v1/marketplace/listings/{id}/offers/**: Unable to verify; view not found yet.
- **3B.6 POST /api/v1/marketplace/listings/{id}/report/**: Unable to verify; view not found yet.
- **3C.1 POST /api/v1/sellers/register/**: ✅ PASS. Uses `[IsAuthenticated]` and blocks duplicate profiles inside `.create()`.
- **3C.2 GET /api/v1/seller/orders/**: ✅ PASS. Requires `[IsAuthenticated, IsApprovedSeller]`. Returns `Order.objects.filter(store=store)`.
- **3C.3 POST /api/v1/seller/orders/{id}/ship/**: ✅ PASS. Requires `[IsAuthenticated, IsApprovedSeller]` and queries `Order.objects.get(id=order_id, store=store)`.
- **3D.1 GET /api/v1/admin/dashboard/**: ✅ PASS. Requires `[IsAuthenticated, IsAdminOrModerator]`.
- **3D.2 POST /api/v1/admin/sellers/{id}/approve/**: ❌ FAIL. [AdminSellerApproveView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/sellers/admin_views.py#61-84) in [sellers/admin_views.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/sellers/admin_views.py) uses `[IsAuthenticated, IsAdminOrModerator]`. Any moderator can approve sellers instead of specifically [IsSellerModerator](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/core/permissions.py#169-179).
- **3D.3 POST /api/v1/admin/refunds/{id}/process/**: ✅ PASS. Requires `[IsAuthenticated, IsAdminUser]`. Only Admins can process refunds.
- **3D.4 GET /api/v1/admin/users/**: ❌ FAIL. [AdminUserListView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/admin_panel/views.py#133-173) uses `[IsAuthenticated, IsAdminOrModerator]` which means ALL moderators can see users, bypassing the specific `manage_users` permission constraint mentioned in the prompt.
- **3D.5 GET /api/v1/admin/verifications/{id}/**: ❌ FAIL. [AdminVerificationDetailView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/verification_views.py#130-168) uses `[IsAuthenticated, IsAdminOrModerator]`. Any moderator can view/approve verifications instead of a specifically scoped moderator role.

## Module 04: Financial Security
- **4.1 Wallet Transactions Immutable**: ✅ PASS. `WalletTransaction.save()` explicitly raises `PermissionError` if `self.pk` exists.
- **4.2 Race Conditions (Atomic Lock)**: ✅ PASS. [process_checkout](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/orders/services/checkout.py#47-269) is wrapped in `transaction.atomic()` and [create_wallet_transaction](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/core/wallet_engine.py#22-94) uses `select_for_update()`.
- **4.3 Platform Commission Split**: ✅ PASS. [process_checkout](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/orders/services/checkout.py#47-269) routes commission to Platform wallet and seller_net to Seller wallet separately.
- **4.4 Negative Balance Prevention**: ✅ PASS. [create_wallet_transaction](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/core/wallet_engine.py#22-94) validates `balance_before < amount` for debits and raises [InsufficientBalanceError](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/core/wallet_engine.py#17-20).
- **4.5 Direct Wallet Updates Blocked**: ⚠️ WARN. Wallet model has `help_text` warning against direct updates, and [refresh_balance](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/wallet/models.py#76-90) synchronizes it with ledger, but there's no hard database-level trigger or model [save()](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/models.py#625-634) override strictly blocking direct updates to the [balance](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/wallet/models.py#76-90) field bypassing the engine.

## Module 05: Security Vulnerabilities
- **5.1 IDOR on Order Details**: ✅ PASS. [BuyerOrderDetailView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/orders/views.py#115-139) restricts to `Order.objects.get(pk=order_id, buyer=request.user)`.
- **5.2 IDOR on Cart Items**: ✅ PASS. [CartRemoveItemView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/mall/views.py#699-722) restricts modification to items in `request.user`'s cart.
- **5.3 Admin Order Status Update**: ✅ PASS. [AdminForceStatusView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/orders/views.py#436-474) calls `order.transition_status()` which enforces state machine rules and prevents invalid transitions.
- **5.4 XSS in Chat/Reviews**: ❌ FAIL. Output of `grep_search` showed no usage of `bleach`. Text fields like `comment` (Review) and `content` (Chat) lack backend HTML sanitization.

## Module 06: Data Integrity & Business Logic
- **6.1 Negative Prices**: ❌ FAIL. `StoreProduct.base_price`, `ProductVariant.price_override`, and `MarketplaceOffer.offered_price` lack `MinValueValidator`. Prices can be set to negative values.
- **6.2 Negative Stock Quantities**: ❌ FAIL. `StoreProduct.stock_quantity` and `ProductVariant.stock_quantity` are standard `IntegerField`s without a `MinValueValidator`.
- **6.3 Soft Deletion Cascade**: ❌ FAIL. [SoftDeleteMixin](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/core/models.py#89-134) only updates `deleted_at` on the `self` instance. It does not cascade soft deletes to related objects (e.g., hiding a store's products when the seller is soft-deleted). Django's `on_delete=models.CASCADE` only applies to hard deletes.
- **6.4 Marketplace Ad Lifecycle Bypass**: ⚠️ WARN. Users cannot manually set an ad to 'active' bypassing admin approval during [partial_update](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/mall/views.py#274-306) because [MarketplaceProductListSerializer](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/marketplace/product_serializers.py#167-195) (used by default for updates) sets all fields to `read_only`. This implicitly prevents the bypass but also completely breaks the user's ability to edit their own listings.

## Module 07: Celery Tasks & Scheduled Jobs
- **7.1 Expired Sessions Cleanup**: ❌ FAIL. No Celery beat task exists in `authentication` to clean up expired sessions.
- **7.2 Auto-Expire Marketplace Ads**: ✅ PASS. [expire_marketplace_posts](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/marketplace/tasks.py#17-47) exists in [apps/marketplace/tasks.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/marketplace/tasks.py) and correctly uses `select_for_update()`.
- **7.3 Auto-Cancel Unpaid Orders**: ❌ FAIL. No Celery task exists in [apps/orders/tasks.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/orders/tasks.py) to auto-cancel unpaid orders after a timeout.
- **7.4 Expire Flash Sales**: ✅ PASS. [end_flash_sales](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/coupons/tasks.py#22-35) exists in [apps/coupons/tasks.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/coupons/tasks.py).

## Module 08: Production Readiness
- **8.1 DEBUG=False in Production**: ✅ PASS. [config/settings/production.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/config/settings/production.py) explicitly sets `DEBUG = False`.
- **8.2 CORS Origins Restricted**: ✅ PASS. `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` read from environment, `CORS_ALLOW_ALL_ORIGINS` is not allowed.
- **8.3 Proper DB Indexes**: ✅ PASS. Core querying tables like [Order](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/orders/models.py#36-185), [WalletTransaction](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/wallet/models.py#116-206), and [StoreProduct](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/mall/models.py#146-230) utilize appropriate composite database indexes on their most filtered columns.
- **8.4 N+1 Query Mitigation**: ✅ PASS. `select_related` and `prefetch_related` are properly employed across major List endpoints like [MarketplaceListingViewSet](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/marketplace/product_views.py#74-307) and `BuyerOrderHistoryView`.

## Module 09: Performance & Query Optimization
- **9.1 Image Upload Sizes**: ❌ FAIL. [MarketplaceProductCreateSerializer](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/marketplace/product_serializers.py#67-161) does not explicitly validate the maximum file size dynamically (e.g., stopping 50MB files at the serializer level). Relies entirely on web server (`client_max_body_size`) which is a potential application-layer vulnerability.
- **9.2 Pagination on List Endpoints**: ✅ PASS. `DEFAULT_PAGINATION_CLASS` and `PAGE_SIZE=20` are correctly set up in [config/settings/base.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/config/settings/base.py).

## Module 10: Integration Smoke Tests
- **10.1 Missing Migrations**: ❌ FAIL. Models were added across Phases 07-10 (e.g., [Notification](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/admin_panel/models.py#142-190), [SearchLog](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/analytics/models.py#81-112), [ProductView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/analytics/models.py#20-75), [SellerDashboardStats](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/analytics/models.py#150-170)) but new migration files have not been generated yet.
- **10.2 Broken Imports**: ✅ PASS. Static analysis indicates imports between core and apps are intact.

