## 🚨 PRIORITY FIX LIST (Critical Blockers)

1. **[DATA] Negative Price & Stock Vulnerability:** Implement `MinValueValidator(0)` on `StoreProduct.stock_quantity`, `ProductVariant.stock_quantity`, `StoreProduct.base_price`, and all offer amount fields to prevent users from hacking minus prices to drain the system.
2. **[AUTH] Auto-Assign Normal User Role:** Modify [apps/authentication/views.py](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/views.py) [RegisterView](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/views.py#30-62) and `StudentRegistrationSerializer` to map newly registered users to the `Normal User` role.
3. **[AUTH] JWT Token Blacklisting:** Add `RefreshToken(refresh_token).blacklist()` logic into the `/auth/logout/` view to immediately invalidate compromised tokens instead of waiting for expiry.
4. **[RBAC] Protect Admin Endpoints:** Decorate or add `permission_classes = [IsAdminOrModerator]` to `AdminActionOnSellerView`, `AdminVerificationActionView`, and `AdminRefundProcessView`. Currently, regular authenticated users might be able to process verifications or refunds.
5. **[DATA] Edit Own Marketplace Listings:** Fix [MarketplaceProductListSerializer](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/marketplace/product_serializers.py#167-195) usage in [partial_update()](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/mall/views.py#274-306). Currently, all fields are `read_only_fields`, silently preventing users from editing their marketplace ads.
6. **[DB] Generate Migrations:** Run `python manage.py makemigrations` and `python manage.py migrate` to spin up tables for Notification, ProductView, SearchLot, and Admin queues.

---

## ⚠️ WARNINGS (Medium Risk)

1. **[SEC] XSS Sanitization lacking in comments and reviews:** Inject `bleach` in serializers to strip HTML from Markdown text in `comment` and `content` fields.
2. **[SEC] Unlimited File Size Unchecked:** `ImageField` does not have a size constraint validator inside serializers, potentially causing DoS.
3. **[DATA] Soft Deletion Cascade Missing:** When a [Seller](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/sellers/models.py#305-351) is soft-deleted, their [Store](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/sellers/models.py#236-299) and [StoreProduct](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/mall/models.py#146-230) do not get soft-deleted, thus remaining active. Ride the `post_save` or override [soft_delete()](file:///c:/Parsonal%20Website/CampusHat/backend/apps/authentication/models.py#227-232) to cascade.

---

**End of Audit Report.** Output saved for Development Team.

